args: *yawn* Goodness, I'm still tired.\nWell, I'd better get the fire going...
Didn't realize I was so surprisin'.
Apologies; I didn't think anyone other than\nmyself was awake.
Not many folks up at sunrise, I guess.\nYou gettin' ready to start breakfast?
Isn't this a bit early for a meeting?
I rise before my master and take\ntime to dress so I can greet him\nin a flawless condition.
That's how it is when you serve.
Plus, a guy who's refreshed and rarin' to\ngo in the morning is more reliable than\nsome bleary-eyed joker, yeah?
You're making me feel more alert already.
Fortuitous. What say we greet the prince\nwith a little bow together, then?
Whew! Let us end today's training here.\n...I must admit, Addis, your skill with\na blade is extremely formidable.
You're no slouch with that poker, either.\nPretty handy to have someone around\nwho can wield a weapon like that.
I'm humbled and honored at the chance\nto cross blades. You have my thanks.
The honor is mine. However, there's no\nneed to thank me for sparring with you.
Every fight I experience makes me\nstronger; it'd be wrong not to express\nmy thanks for that.
Well, in that case, let me thank you\nformally as well.
My skills improved during our last match,\nand for that I am grateful. My thanks.
Cleo said she was treatin' us to a real\nfeast tonight, so let's hurry back.
*sniff* Hold on a tick, yeah?\nMy sniffer found somethin'.
*sniiiiff* Yeah, it's comin' from that shop\nover there. Let's go check it out!
We got a feast waitin' for us at the castle.\nLet's just get back to that.
Bwa ha ha! Ol' Ranzal NEVER turns down a\nsecond meal! C'mon, it'll only take a sec.\nDon't be such a fuddy-duddy.
I ain't a fuddy-duddy; Cleo's just workin'\nher tail off making food for us.
You really wanna wander back all bloated\nand gassy and say you ain't hungry?
No, but I... I mean, the food smells so...\nAh, hell. Yer right. I was bein' rude.
Then if we're done with this little crisis,\nlet's make for the castle already.
You're always so respectful, Addis.\nAre all samurai from Hinomoto like that?
Nah, not everybody. We've got plenty'a\nfolks who come at my master like a\npack of wild boars.

Honestly, before I went to Hinomoto,
I was a pretty tactless ruffian myself.
Didn't have the first clue when it came
to manners and honor and all that.

Nope. I was born in a small country a
long way from both there and here.
Just a real garbage dump of a place,
if I'm bein' totally honest.
Place was poor in both money and heart.\nIf you had a crumb'a food to your name,\nyou fought like hell to keep it.
That's why I took up the swordâ€”to survive.
I lashed out at anyone and everyone,\nand hurt a lot of folks along the way.
Yeah, I'm a different guy now.
A merchant eventually gave me a chance,\nand I took a job guardin' his ship.
'Course it sank on the way to Alberia.
Yep. When I came to, I found myself\nwashed up on the shore of Hinomoto.
Some government fellow arrested me for\nenterin' the country illegally. Tried to tell\n'em what happened, but they didn't care.
Probably woulda ended up with my head\non a pike if not for him.
He believed my story and told the\ngovernment folks to let me go.
Then he gave me work as a guard,\nsince I had no place else to go.
So that's how you came to serve him?
You got it. And sure, I owe him for savin'\nmy life and givin' me a job and all that,\nbut there's more to it.
I learned an entirely new way of existence\nfrom watchin' him. I never would have\ngot that in my old life.
I learned true love and respect from him.\nLearned what it means to be a samurai\nand why it's vital to protect the peace.
Made me realize I wasn't goin' through\nthis life alone.
So the value I place on manners now is\nmy way of showin' gratitude.
Kind of a silent thank you,\nif you know what I mean.
That's a remarkable way of looking at\nthings. I may need to adopt it.
Too bad all that politeness can't scrub\nthe rough talk outta my speech! Bwa ha!
